<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911004-0129</DOCNO><DOCID>911004-0129.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- LTV Corp.:   Unit Gets Army Contract   With Value of $13.5 Million</HL><DATE>10/04/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9A</SO><CO>   LTV</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)BANKRUPTCIES (BCY)STEEL MANUFACTURERS (STL)</IN><NS>BANKRUPTCY DECLARATIONS AND PROCEEDINGS (BCY)DEFENSE CONTRACTS (DFC)</NS><GV>DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)</GV><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   LTV Corp., Dallas, said the U.S. Army Missile Commandawarded its LTV Aerospace andamp; Defense Co. subsidiary a $13.5million contract for 376 payload interface modules, anelectronic device that allows certain missile launchers tofire advanced weapons.   The steel, energy, aerospace and defense concern said thecontract work will be completed at its facility in Camden,Ark. First deliveries of the modules are due next September,with contract completion in early 1994, the company said.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>